The first North London Derby of this season will be played on Sunday at the Emirates. Arsenal, who lost for the first time against Liverpool, will be looking to bounce back against their rivals. Spurs also suffered a shock 1-0 home defeat to Newcastle last weekend. Kick off is 4.30pm West African time. Arsenal XI to face Tottenham: Leno; Maitland-Niles, Sokratis, Luiz, Kolasinac; Torreira, Xhaka, Guendouzi; Pepe, Lacazette, Aubameyang Tottenham XI to face Arsenal: Lloris; Alderweireld, Sanchez, Vertonghen, Rose; Sissoko, Winks; Lamela, Eriksen, Son; Kane Sunday, September 1
